.head 3 -  !
.head 3 +  Function: MakeStringList  
.head 4 -  Description: This functions make a any character separated list into sStringList from the array saStrings[*].
VERY IMPORTANT ASSUMPTION : saStrings[*] is assumed to be terminated by a NULL value.
PARAMETERS :
  saStirng[*] : array of strings terminated by a NULL value
  sSeparator : string used as the list string separator
                       eg: jan, michelle, dani the comma is the separator
  sQuoteType : string used as the type of character for the quotes around the strings.
                         eg: "jan", "michelle", "dani" the double quote is the quote type character
                         note use sQueryType of blank to obtain a non quoted string list.
.head 4 -  Returns
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  String: saStrings[*]  
.head 5 -  String: sSeparator  
.head 5 -  String: sQuoteType  
.head 5 -  Receive String: sStringList  
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: naStringPos  
.head 5 -  Boolean: bFirst  
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 5 -  Set bFirst = TRUE
.head 5 -  Set sStringList = ''
.head 5 -  Set naStringPos = 0
.head 5 +  While saStrings[ naStringPos ] != ''
.head 6 +  If bFirst
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sQuoteType || saStrings[ naStringPos ] || sQuoteType
.head 7 -  Set bFirst = FALSE
.head 6 +  Else
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sStringList || sSeparator || sQuoteType || saStrings[ naStringPos ] || sQuoteType
.head 6 -  Set naStringPos = naStringPos + 1
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( FALSE )
.head 3 +  ! Function: MakeDateTimeList  
.head 4 -  Description: This functions make a any character separated list into sStringList from the array dtaDT[*].
VERY IMPORTANT ASSUMPTION : dtaDT[*] is assumed to be terminated by a DATETIME_NULL value.
PARAMETERS :
  dtaDT[*] : array of DateTime stamps terminated by a DATETIME_NULL value
  sSeparator : string used as the list string separator
                       eg: jan, michelle, dani the comma is the separator
  sQuoteType : string used as the type of character for the quotes around the strings.
                         eg: "jan", "michelle", "dani" the double quote is the quote type character
                         note use sQueryType of blank to obtain a non quoted string list.
.head 4 -  Returns 
.head 4 +  Parameters 
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtaDT[*]  
.head 5 -  String: sSeparator  
.head 5 -  String: sQuoteType  
.head 5 -  Receive String: sStringList  
.head 4 -  Static Variables 
.head 4 +  Local variables 
.head 5 -  Number: naStringPos  
.head 5 -  Boolean: bFirst  
.head 5 -  String: sDate  
.head 4 +  Actions 
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( TRUE )
.head 5 -  Set bFirst = TRUE
.head 5 -  Set sStringList = ''
.head 5 -  Set naStringPos = 0
.head 5 +  While dtaDT[ naStringPos ] != DATETIME_Null
.head 6 -  Call SalDateToStr( dtaDT[ naStringPos ], sDate )
.head 6 +  If bFirst
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sQuoteType || sDate || sQuoteType
.head 7 -  Set bFirst = FALSE
.head 6 +  Else 
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sStringList || sSeparator || sQuoteType || sDate || sQuoteType
.head 6 -  Set naStringPos = naStringPos + 1
.head 5 -  Call OurWaitCursor( FALSE )
.head 3 +  Function: MakeNumberList  
.head 4 -  Description: This functions make a any character separated list into sStringList from the array naNumber[*].
VERY IMPORTANT ASSUMPTION : naDT[*] is assumed to be terminated by a NUMBER_NULL value.
PARAMETERS :
  naNumber[*] : array of DateTime stamps terminated by a NUMBER_NULL value
  nPrecision : number of precision decimal places applied through out naNumber[*]
  sSeparator : string used as the list string separator
                       eg: jan, michelle, dani the comma is the separator
  sQuoteType : string used as the type of character for the quotes around the strings.
                         eg: "jan", "michelle", "dani" the double quote is the quote type character
                         note use sQueryType of blank to obtain a non quoted string list.
.head 4 -  Returns
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: naNumber[*]  
.head 5 -  Number: nPrecision  
.head 5 -  String: sSeparator  
.head 5 -  String: sQuoteType  
.head 5 -  Receive String: sStringList  
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: naStringPos  
.head 5 -  Boolean: bFirst  
.head 5 -  String: sNumber  
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set bFirst = TRUE
.head 5 -  Set sStringList = ''
.head 5 -  Set naStringPos = 0
.head 5 +  While naNumber[ naStringPos ] != NUMBER_Null
.head 6 -  Set sNumber = SalNumberToStrX( naNumber[ naStringPos ], nPrecision )
.head 6 +  If bFirst
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sQuoteType || sNumber || sQuoteType
.head 7 -  Set bFirst = FALSE
.head 6 +  Else
.head 7 -  Set sStringList = sStringList || sSeparator || sQuoteType || sNumber || sQuoteType
.head 6 -  Set naStringPos = naStringPos + 1
